headline: Board of Directors of The Coca-Cola Company Elects New Officer and Approves 64th Consecutive Annual Dividend Increase
summary: ATLANTA, February 19, 2026--The Board of Directors of The Coca-Cola Company today announced the election of a new company officer and the approval of the company’s 64th consecutive annual dividend increase.

headline: Coca-Cola CEO Shift Pairs Digital Push With Dividend Growth Story
summary: Coca-Cola (NYSE:KO) has named Henrique Braun as incoming CEO, with plans to speed up product launches and increase regional decision-making. The company is creating a new Chief Digital Officer role to support a broader digital transformation across marketing, sales, and operations. These leadership and structural changes come as Coca-Cola continues its record of dividend growth.
